http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Road-Safety-Week/article14006188.ece

The Telangana State Road Transport Corporation will observe the 27{+t}{+h}Road Safety Week between January 20 and 26. During the week, drivers with accident-free records will be identified and awarded cash prizes and certificates of appreciation.Over the week, traffic, police and legal experts and those representing commuters will counsel drivers, conductors and mechanical staff in garages on road safety. Special medical camps will also be conducted and special training classes will be held on safety driving at Zonal Staff Training colleges of the RTC with special emphasis on maintenance, said a press release. - Special Correspondent